## Mandatory Visual Parity Check

After completing any UI prompt:

1. Open `docs/design-reference.html` in one browser window
2. Open the actual app (`index.html`) in another window
3. Place them side-by-side at 1280×720
4. Compare: gradients, colors, spacing, typography weights, shadow intensity, hover states
5. If anything drifts beyond ±4px spacing or any color/gradient mismatch, the prompt is NOT done. Re-port from the reference.

This check is non-negotiable. Skipping it produces "kinda right but off" results.

## What This File Is NOT

`docs/design-reference.html` is a visual prototype. It is NOT the production code. Do NOT:
- Copy its inline `<script>` block as the app's logic (the app uses split files: state.js, router.js, etc.)
- Copy its single-file structure (the app is multi-file)
- Treat its placeholder/stub functionality as complete (it only has 1 case, the app needs 4)
- Edit `docs/design-reference.html` to "fix" anything — it is read-only spec
